This app is amazing! It provides a full linux environment, not just a special android- version of linux, with its own filesystem. With the XServer app & the package LXDE, you can even run GUI on top of Debian. The only issue I faced was that you cannot install the full version of Kali. I would also like to see the ability to move filesystems between the SD card and Internal Storage and some way to access the android filesystem (ex. a folder that like /mnt). UserLAnd is the best (and possibly only) app to put linux on android, and it arose all my expectations.
